  "body": "### Version of Hardhat\n\n2.13.0\n\n### What happened?\n\nWhen I try to run transaction it screams about setting a hugh upfront cost in my account when attempt to run it.\r\nIt seems to be taking from the feeData, maxFeePerGas * gasLimit which in my case, since I have had to recalculate maxFeePerGas for my developed smart contract method to run against, it is asking me to lay down upfront cost of almost 1240074063290634200000 wei almost $2-2.5M. How can I resolve this ludricous amount?\r\n\r\nThank you\n\n### Minimal reproduction steps\n\nWhen I try to run transaction it screams about setting a hugh upfront cost in my account when attempt to run it.\r\nIt seems to be taking from the feeData, maxFeePerGas * gasLimit which in my case, since I have had to recalculate maxFeePerGas for my developed smart contract method to run against, it is asking me to lay down upfront cost of almost 1240074063290634200000 wei almost $2-2.5M. How can I resolve this ludricous amount?\r\n\r\nThank you\n\n### Search terms\n\nhardhat, gasLimit, upfront cost",
